There are two items in this ticket.

### Write a program that takes the raw schema and generates a corresponding Doctrine entity.

Write a program that takes the raw schema and generates a corresponding Doctrine entity. Some code from the current (basic) approach can be reused: https://github.com/openemr/openemr/issues/472#issuecomment-277575267

Make sure the data types are correctly mapped per http://docs.doctrine-project.org/projects/doctrine-dbal/en/latest/reference/types.html#mapping-matrix

### Determine where the 25 tables that are not referenced in initialization script

Determine where the 25 tables that are not referenced in https://github.com/openemr/openemr/blob/master/sql/database.sql are specified. Here's some more information on this:

When once runs the following query:

```
SELECT count(*) AS total 
  FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLES
 WHERE TABLE_SCHEMA = 'openemr';
```

The result is 219.

When one runs the following code:

```
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/openemr/openemr/master/sql/database.sql
```

...and `node index.js` for:

```
var FileSystem = require('fs');
var OperatingSystem = require('os');

function countTables(contents) {
  var contentsAsArray = contents.split(OperatingSystem.EOL);

  var count = 0;

  contentsAsArray.forEach(function(line) {
    if (line.indexOf('CREATE TABLE') > -1) {
      count++;
    }
  });

  return count;
}

function construct(command) {
  var result = countTables(FileSystem.readFileSync('database.sql', 'utf8'));
  console.log('There are ' + result + ' tables');
}

construct();
```

The result is 194 :/

